    "id": "f_csv_b718230996",
    "slug": "i-glimpsed-the-man-s-face-with-the-shine-of-death-on-it-they-laid-him-down-ther",
    "texto": "I glimpsed the man's face with the shine of death on it. They laid him down there in the open. They had brought him there to be close to his death, I understood this also at the same moment. For who would wish to see a companion gasp his last on a jolting cart? We desire to keep the dying and the newly dead close before our eyes so as to give them full meed of pity. Our Lord was brought down to be pitied, on the Cross He was too far away.",
    "autor": "Barry Unsworth",
    "autorSlug": "barry-unsworth",
    "explicacao": "Pergunta retórica de Barry Unsworth que provoca passagem do tempo e prioridades. Ao questionar “I glimpsed the man's face with the shine of death on it. They laid him down there in the open. Th…”, o texto convida o leitor a revisar crenças sobre tempo, christ, dying, com foco em luto e dying.",
